<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1925,2022]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,356]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1925,1950]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species can be distinguished by the white posterior margin of the eyes; the pale yellow frons (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1961,1985]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1492,1515]" captionTargetBox="[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-329@11.[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Myiomma pallidopleura (holotype). 29, dorsal aspect; 30, lateral aspect; 31, head and pronotum; dorsal aspect; 32, head, lateral aspect; 33, head, frontal aspect." pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
); the pale antennal segment I with only a narrow, apical, brown band; the dorsally and ventrally pale antennal segment II, with the lateral margins dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[843,990,1998,2022]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1492,1515]" captionTargetBox="[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-329@11.[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Myiomma pallidopleura (holotype). 29, dorsal aspect; 30, lateral aspect; 31, head and pronotum; dorsal aspect; 32, head, lateral aspect; 33, head, frontal aspect." pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Figs. 29, 32</figureCitation>
); the dark pronotum, with a narrowly explanate, pale lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[495,578,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1492,1515]" captionTargetBox="[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-329@11.[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Myiomma pallidopleura (holotype). 29, dorsal aspect; 30, lateral aspect; 31, head and pronotum; dorsal aspect; 32, head, lateral aspect; 33, head, frontal aspect." pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); the uniformly pale yellow propleura (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1152,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1492,1515]" captionTargetBox="[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-329@11.[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Myiomma pallidopleura (holotype). 29, dorsal aspect; 30, lateral aspect; 31, head and pronotum; dorsal aspect; 32, head, lateral aspect; 33, head, frontal aspect." pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Figs. 30, 32</figureCitation>
); and the pale translucent hemelytra, with only the base of the clavus dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[782,866,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1492,1515]" captionTargetBox="[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-329@11.[268,1318,409,1471]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Myiomma pallidopleura (holotype). 29, dorsal aspect; 30, lateral aspect; 31, head and pronotum; dorsal aspect; 32, head, lateral aspect; 33, head, frontal aspect." pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
